  <title>
   <narrative xml:lang="EN">Promoting Greater Civic Participation in Sierra Leone</narrative>
  </title>
  <description>
   <narrative xml:lang="EN">This project seeks to support the National Electoral Commission (NEC) of Sierra Leone to run a comprehensive voter and civic education campaign to improve Sierra Leoneans&#x2019; knowledge about the 2023 general elections as well as to encourage voters to register and participate in the 2023 general elections. The project will help to strengthen the Sierra Leone democratic process through raising awareness on the significance of electoral processes among Sierra Leone voters and increase their participation in the 2023 general elections.
This approach is seeking to utilise an independent but also much broad based system for the 2023 general election which include Paramount Chief Member of Parliament, Local Council, Parliamentarian and Presidential elections by promoting civic education, peace messages and in supporting the efforts of the EMB and other actors targeting vulnerable groups including women, people with disability, young people and first time voters in the country.</narrative>
  </description>
